cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about a multilingual dialogue system and involves natural language processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel architecture for dialogue generation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed architecture is based on a sequence to sequence framework with shared-private memory. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks for dialogue generation. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely as the paper does not mention any audio or speech-related aspects.
